I)\n|style=\"background:#D3D3D3; border:5px groove #FFDF00;\"|[[File:USA - Army Finance Corps.png|x40px]]\n!style=\"background:#25185d; color:white;\"|\n|[[Infantry Branch (United States)|Infantry]] (IN)\n|style=\"background:#A2e3e8;\"|[[File:USA - Army Infantry Insignia.png|x38px]]\n|style=\"background:#25185d; color:white;\"|\n|[[Foreign Area Officer]] (FA 48)\n|-\n|[[Inspector general#United States|Inspector General]] (IG)\n|style=\"background:navy; border:5px groove lightblue;\"|[[File:USA - Inspector General Branch Insignia.png|x38px]]\n|style=\"background:#25185d; color:white;\"|\n|[[United States Army Logistics Branch|Logistics]] (LG)\n|style=\"background: #BF1238; border:5px groove #CD7F32;\"|[[File:USA - Logistics Branch Insignia.png|x50px]]\n|style=\"background:#25185d; color:white;\"|\n|Operations Research/Systems Analysis (FA 49)\n|-\n|[[United States Army Judge Advocate General's Corps|Judge Advocate General's Corps]] (JA)\n|style=\"background:navy; border:5px groove white;\"|[[File:JAGC Staff Corps Insignia Army.gif|x35px]]\n!style=\"background:#25185d; color:white;\"|\n|[[United States Army Military Intelligence|Military Intelligence Corps]] (MI)\n|style=\"background:#1E90FF; border:5px groove #D3D3D3;\"|[[File:MI Corps Insignia.svg|x55px]]\n|style=\"background:#25185d; color:white;\"|\n|Force Management (FA 50)\n|-\n|[[Medical Corps (United States Army)|Medical Corps]] (MC)\n|style=\"background:maroon; border:5px groove white;\"|[[File:USA - Army Medical Corps.png|x50px]]\n!style=\"background:#25185d; color:white;\"|\n|[[Army Medical Department (United States)#Medical Service Corps (MS)|Medical Service Corps]] (MS)\n|style=\"background:maroon; border:5px groove white;\"|[[File:USA - Army Medical Specialist Corps.png|x49px]]\n|style=\"background:#25185d; color:white;\"|\n|Acquisition ([[List of United States Army careers#Army Acquisition Corps (FA and CMF 51)|FA 51]])<ref name=AACSL/>\n|-\n|[[United States Army Military Police Corps|Military Police Corps]] (MP)\n|style=\"background:green; border:5px groove yellow;\"|[[File:USAMPC-Branch-Insignia.png|x38px]]\n!style=\"background:#25185d; color:white;\"|\n|[[Army Nurse Corps (United States)|Army Nurse Corps]] (AN)\n|style=\"background:maroon; border:5px groove white;\"|[[File:USA - Army Medical Nurse.png|x50px]]\n|style=\"background:#25185d; color:white;\"|\n|Simulation Operations (FA 57)\n|-\n|[[Psychological Operations (United States)|Psychological Operations]] (PO)\n|style=\"background:#4F7942; border:5px groove #D3D3D3;\"|[[File:USA - Psych Ops Branch Insignia.png|50px]]\n|style=\"background:#25185d; color:white;\"|\n|[[Army Medical Department (United States)#Medical Specialist Corps (SP)|Medical Specialist Corps]] (SP)\n|style=\"background:maroon; border:5px groove white;\"|[[File:USA - Army Medical Specialist.png|x50px]]\n!style=\"background:#25185d; color:white;\"|\n|Army Marketing (FA 58)<ref>[https://www.army.mil/article/231034/new_marketing_job_lets_officers_steward_army_brand New marketing job lets officers steward Army brand], Army.mil, by Thomas Brading (Army News Service), dated 16 December 2019, last accessed 1 January 2020</ref>\n|-\n|[[United States Army Quartermaster Corps|Quartermaster Corps]] (QM)\n|style=\"background:#F0DC82;\"|[[File:USA - Quartermaster Corps Branch Insignia.png|x42px]]\n|style=\"background:#25185d; color:white;\"|\n|[[Staff Specialist Corps]] (SS)<br>(USAR and ARNG only)\n|style=\"background:green;\"|[[File:StaffSpecUSAR ARNGBC.gif|x45px]]\n!style=\"background:#25185d; color:white;\"|\n|Health Services (FA 70)\n|-\n|[[United States Army Special Forces|Special Forces]] (SF)\n|style=\"background:#004B49;\"|[[File:USA - Special Forces Branch Insignia.png|x35px]]\n|style=\"background:#25185d; color:white;\"|\n|[[United States Army Ordnance Corps|Ordnance Corps]] (OD)\n|style=\"background:crimson; border:5px groove yellow;\"|[[File:Ordnance Branch Insignia.svg|x50px]]\n!style=\"background:#25185d; color:white;\"|\n|Laboratory Sciences (FA 71)\n|-\n|[[Veterinary Corps (United States Army)|Veterinary Corps]] (VC)\n|style=\"background:maroon; border:5px groove white;\"|[[File:USA - Army Medical Veterinary.png|x50px]]\n|style=\"background:#25185d; color:white;\"|\n|[[Public affairs (military)|Public Affairs]] (PA)\n|style=\"background:#008080; border:5px groove yellow;\"|[[File:PublicAffairsBC.svg|45px]]\n!style=\"background:#25185d; color:white;\"|\n|Preventive Medicine Sciences (FA 72)\n|-\n|[[United States Army Transportation Corps|Transportation Corps]] (TC)\n|style=\"background:#800020; border:5px groove yellow;\"|[[File:USA - Transportation Corps Branch Insignia.png|x50px]]\n!style=\"background:#25185d; color:white;\"|\n|[[United States Army Signal Corps|Signal Corps]] (SC)\n|style=\"background:#FF7F00; border:5px groove white;\"|[[File:Insignia signal.svg|x40px]]\n!style=\"background:#25185d; color:white;\"|\n|Behavioral Sciences (FA 73)\n|-\n!colspan=\"7\"|Special branch insignias ''(for specific duty assignments)''\n|-\n|colspan=\"7\"|[[Aide-de-camp]]: [[File:Lapel insignia of an aide-de-camp to a U.S. Army Brigadier General.jpg|50px]] [[File:MajGenAide.jpg|50px]] [[File:LtGenAide.jpg|50px]] [[File:GenAide.jpg|50px]] [[File:GA-Aide.GIF|50px]] [[File:Branch insignia, Aide to Vice Chief, National Guard Bureau.jpg|50px]] [[File:Branch insignia, Aide to Chief, National Guard Bureau.jpg|50px]] [[File:Aide VCoS-Army BC.png|50px]] [[File:AideCoSArmyBC.gif|50px]] [[File:Aide UnderSec-Army BC.png|50px]] [[File:AideSecyArmyBC.gif|50px]] [[File:Aide VJCoS BC.png|50px]] [[File:AideJCoSBC.gif|50px]] [[File:AideSecyDefenseBC.gif|50px]] [[File:Aide-de-camp insignia for VP aide.gif|50px]] [[File:AidePOTUSBC.gif|50px]]\n|-\n|General Staff\n![[File:USA - Army General Staff Branch Insignia.png|50px]]\n!style=\"background:#25185d; color:white;\"|\n|[[National Guard Bureau]]\n|style=\"background:darkblue;\"|[[File:NatlGuardBureauBC.gif|50px]]\n!style=\"background:#25185d; color:white;\"|\n|[[Senior Enlisted Advisor]]: [[File:USA - Army Immaterial Command Insignia.png|49px]] [[File:Sma-bos.jpg|50px]] [[File:SEAC-collar1.jpg|50px]]\n|}\n{{Clear}}\n\nBefore 1933, members of the Army National Guard were considered state militia until they were mobilized into U.S. Army, typically on the onset of war. Since the 1933 amendment to the [[National Defense Act of 1916]], all Army National Guard soldiers have held dual status. They serve as National Guardsmen under the authority of the governor of their state or territory and as a reserve members of the U.S. Army under the authority of the president, in the Army National Guard of the United States.\n\nSince the adoption of the total force policy, in the aftermath of the Vietnam War, reserve component soldiers have taken a more active role in U.S. military operations. For example, Reserve and Guard units took part in the [[Gulf War]], peacekeeping in [[Kosovo]], Afghanistan and the [[2003 invasion of Iraq]].\n\n===Army commands and army service component commands===\n[[File:Headquarters US Army SSI.png|25px]] [[United States Department of the Army|Headquarters, United States Department of the Army]] (HQDA):\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Army Commands\n!Current commander\n!Location of headquarters\n|-\n|[[File:United States Army Forces Command SSI.svg|20px]] [[United States Army Forces Command]] (FORSCOM) || GEN [[Michael X. Garrett]] || [[Fort Bragg]], [[North Carolina]]\n|-\n|[[File:Army Futures Command SSI.png|20px]] [[United States Army Futures Command]] (AFC) || GEN [[John M. Murray]] || [[Austin]], [[Texas]]\n|-\n|[[File:AMC shoulder insignia.svg|20px]] [[U.S. Army Materiel Command|United States Army Materiel Command]] (AMC) || GEN [[Gustave F. Perna]] || [[Redstone Arsenal]], [[Alabama]]\n|-\n|[[File:TRADOC patch.svg|20px]] [[United States Army Training and Doctrine Command]] (TRADOC) || GEN [[Paul E. Funk II]] || [[Fort Eustis]], [[Virginia]]\n|-\n!Army Service Component Commands\n!Current commander\n!Location of headquarters\n|-\n|[[File:U.S. Army Africa Shoulder Sleeve Insignia.jpg|22px]] [[United States Army Africa]] (USARAF)/[[Ninth U.S. Army|Ninth Army]]/United States Army Southern European Task Force || MG [[Roger L. Cloutier, Jr.]]<ref>{{Cite web|url= https://www.africom.mil/media-room/article/31105/usaraf-welcomes-new-commanding-general|website =United States Africa Command|title = USARAF welcomes new commanding general|first = Meredith|last = March|date = 7 August 2018}}</ref>\n|| [[Caserma Ederle]], [[Vicenza]], [[Italy]]\n|-\n|[[File:US3ASSI.svg|20px]] [[United States Army Central]] (ARCENT)/[[Third U.S. Army|Third Army]] ||LTG Terry Ferrell || [[Shaw Air Force Base]], [[South Carolina]]\n|-\n|[[File:USAREUR Insignia.svg|20px]] [[United States Army Europe]] (USAREUR)/[[Seventh United States Army|Seventh Army]] (U.S.) || LTG [[Christopher Cavoli]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eur.army.mil/leaders/|title=Leaders {{!}} U.S. Army Europe Leaders|website=Army.mil|accessdate=2 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180118130035/http://www.eur.army.mil/leaders/|archive-date=18 January 2018|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> || [[Lucius D. Clay Kaserne|Clay Kaserne]], [[Wiesbaden]], [[Germany]]\n|-\n|[[File:United States Army North CSIB.svg|20px]] [[United States Army North]] (ARNORTH)/[[Fifth U.S. Army|Fifth Army]] || LTG [[Laura J. Richardson]] || [[Joint Base San Antonio]], [[Texas]]\n|-\n|[[File:USARPAC insignia.svg|20px]] [[United States Army Pacific]] (USARPAC) || GEN [[Paul J. LaCamera|Paul LaCamera]] || [[Fort Shafter]], [[Hawaii]]\n|-\n|[[File:UNITED STATES ARMY SOUTH SSI.svg|20px]] [[United States Army South]] (ARSOUTH)/[[Sixth United States Army|Sixth Army]] || MG [[Daniel R. Walrath]]|| Joint Base San Antonio, Texas\n|-\n<!--|[[File:Surface Deployment and Distribution Command SSI.svg|20px]] [[Surface Deployment and Distribution Command]] (SDDC) || MG [[Kurt J. Ryan]]<ref>{{cite web|date=7 September 2010|title=Commanding General|publisher=United States A